@onslaught10989

If it doesn't have a skull, click on the FILES at the top of the screen and look at what the files are. If it is a RAR file of a movie it is 99.9% chance of being fake. If it is a WMV file of a movie it is 99.9% chance of being fake. AVI/MKV files are normally OK.

These guys have to get a few uploads under their belt before they get a skull. Just learn a few things about torrents and files, make sure that your anti virus is all up to date and the worst that can happen to you is that you waste a couple of hours of your time downloading a crap torrent.
